menu "LKCAMP educational drivers"

config EDU_PBUF
	tristate "Educational system alert queue character driver"
	default m
	help
	  Builds /dev/edu_pbuf, an educational pseudo character driver
	  based on the LKCAMP device-driver tutorial.

	  The driver simulates a small system alert queue. User space can
	  publish alerts by writing to /dev/edu_pbuf, while another process
	  can read pending alerts, wait for new alerts through blocking read
	  or poll/select, and configure queue behavior through ioctl or
	  sysfs attributes.

	  To build it as a module, choose M. The module will be called
	  edu_pbuf.

endmenu
